text: The Maine Comprehensive Assessment System is the State’s measure of student progress in
label: BODY

text: achieving the State standards, known as Learning Results, adopted by the Maine Legislature in
label: BODY

text: 1997. The Maine Educational Assessment (MEA) is administered in grades 3 through 8 to meet
label: BODY

text: these state assessment requirements. Since the spring of 2006, the SAT Reasoning Test™ (SAT)
label: BODY

text: has been administered to students in their third year of high school in place of the MEA for state
label: BODY

text: and federal purposes. The move from the MEA to the SAT in grade 11 was made to encourage all
label: BODY

text: students in the goal of attaining college and high-level workplace readiness as well as to measure
label: BODY

text: achievement. This year, the mathematics portion of the SAT Reasoning Test™ was augmented with
label: BODY

text: 18 additional mathematics items (the Math-A test) to more fully measure Maine’s Learning Results.
label: BODY

text: The combined tests form the Maine High School Assessment (MHSA).
label: BODY

text: Due to the inclusion of the additional items in mathematics, it was necessary to set new
label: BODY

text: achievement level standards for that discipline this year. The new achievement level standards
label: BODY

text: are the result of a comprehensive process informed by Maine teachers and reviewed by advisory
label: BODY

text: committees. The achievement level standards were not changed for the Critical Reading and
label: BODY

text: These 2006-2007 Maine High School Assessment Summary Reports contain the results of
label: BODY

text: student performance on the SAT in critical reading, mathematics, and writing reported according to
label: BODY

text: the achievement standards described above and disaggregated by student and school characteristics.
label: BODY

text: This report, together with individual student and subject-speciﬁ c student roster reports, provides
label: BODY

text: support for use in program evaluation and planning. All scores contained in these reports are
label: BODY

label: BODY

label: BODY
